column5: Big, meaningful points are up for grabs tonight. Both teams need to stay in the playoff race. Ottawa is down 2-1 right now and Toronto has looked like the better team over the past 5 games.  For the record I'm cheering for the Jets. I'm predicting 5-3 Jets tonight.

Jets and leafs has been a good 1 so far.  How bout them leafs playing like a playoff-worthy team the last few games?  Too bad burkie doesnt have any big trades planned for this months deadline, we could defiantly use a bit of extra fire power off the wing.
I also root for the Jets, but only when they aren't playing the Leafs.  In fact I have 7th row seats on the Jets blue line in Tampa on March 31st.
Dave, Yellowknife to Tampa in March....you're going to go into shock.
I'll probably succumb to heat stroke as soon as the planes door is opened. Hopefully I will forget about the heat as soon as I stick my first tarpon.
You have to love the Winnipeg fans. I'm a Leafs fan all the way, but, the stuffed shirts at the ACC should take some lessons.
